          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812972825" href="/book/show/147537.Franklin_and_Winston">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=europe">europe</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=military-war">military-war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=top-ten-percent">top-ten-percent</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=africa">africa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=review">review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=namerica">namerica</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1062848083" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3167264529465996860">This book is an intimate description of a facinating relationship between Franklin Roosevelt and Winston Churchill and their personal and political relationship prior to and during World War II. It is intimate because nuch of the new material comes from diaries, correspondence and material unavailable previously. The book is almost a day to day account of their experiences during the war. It exposes both the best and worst qualities of each man including cigars, alcohol and some intimate friends</span>
  <span id="freeText3167264529465996860" style="display:none">This book is an intimate description of a facinating relationship between Franklin Roosevelt and Winston Churchill and their personal and political relationship prior to and during World War II. It is intimate because nuch of the new material comes from diaries, correspondence and material unavailable previously. The book is almost a day to day account of their experiences during the war. It exposes both the best and worst qualities of each man including cigars, alcohol and some intimate friendships. This is far and away the best insight to the leadership of the Allies of World War II that I have read and often is so powerful that for us that view this as the only fully justified war of our time, that I often had to catch my breath to reflect on the humor or the tragedy or the possible consequences of their decisions. An excellent biography.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3167264529465996860" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


