<div id="review_3192565631" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3192565631" />
    <a title="NinaB" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7618432-ninab"><img alt="NinaB" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518652932p2/7618432.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3192565631?book_show_action=true">Oct 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="NinaB" class="user" itemprop="url" name="NinaB" href="/user/show/7618432-ninab">NinaB</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812972825" href="/book/show/147537.Franklin_and_Winston">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7618432-ninab?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7618432-ninab?shelf=top-2020">top-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3192565631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer668432945233238056">This Pulitzer Prize-winning author and former editor of Newsweek was my husband’s best friend in high school. He was a staunch Reagan-ite in his youth. His politics has changed some since then, I’m afraid. <br/><br/>Franklin and Winston is the third book I’ve read by him and, by far, my favorite of the three. It’s an intimate look at the friendship of the two bravest leaders of the 20th century who had to deal with a world war that was initially dominated by the Nazis. Their complicated relationship had i</span>
  <span id="freeText668432945233238056" style="display:none">This Pulitzer Prize-winning author and former editor of Newsweek was my husband’s best friend in high school. He was a staunch Reagan-ite in his youth. His politics has changed some since then, I’m afraid. <br /><br />Franklin and Winston is the third book I’ve read by him and, by far, my favorite of the three. It’s an intimate look at the friendship of the two bravest leaders of the 20th century who had to deal with a world war that was initially dominated by the Nazis. Their complicated relationship had its ups and downs, but their mutual commitment to democracy won the war in the end.<br /><br />It makes me sad that Roosevelt died before the war was over and didn’t see the fruit of his hard work. I am also saddened that the British people got rid of Churchill as soon as the enemies were defeated. He deserved more thanks than that. I am grateful, however, that God raised such courageous men who, in their limited abilities and knowledge, fought with tenacity and perseverance for the sake of democracy and toppling down fascist tyrants. <br /><br />We need more leaders such as these men. It seems the recent generations have been long removed from war that we’ve forgotten how hard-fought our freedoms have been. We are ignorant of true tyrants and oppressive systems that many romanticize fascism and communism. May the Lord help us as we face invisible enemies in the forms of dangerous ideologies and tiny viruses in the 21st century. May we find the courage to fight the enemy with dignity, courage and a commitment to democracy.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="668432945233238056" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


