<span id="freeTextContainer8050282626916946145">I bet most of the info in this book came from Sir Gilbert. Roosevelt did not like Winston but the book changes it around blames it on Joseph Kennedy, i guess to save some face for Churchill. Nothing against Sir Gilbert since he is obligated to only write the positive things about Churchill. But this book only paints positive things &amp; do not give you insight/details on the situations. Not impressed, but I wanted more info &amp; details..the whys...and this book doesn’t do it. We are way past WW2, the</span>
  <span id="freeText8050282626916946145" style="display:none">I bet most of the info in this book came from Sir Gilbert. Roosevelt did not like Winston but the book changes it around blames it on Joseph Kennedy, i guess to save some face for Churchill. Nothing against Sir Gilbert since he is obligated to only write the positive things about Churchill. But this book only paints positive things &amp; do not give you insight/details on the situations. Not impressed, but I wanted more info &amp; details..the whys...and this book doesn’t do it. We are way past WW2, the truth about the Japanese code breaking, Churchill knew, those docs are sealed for 99yrs.</span>
